ESP32 -CONTROLLER



1. Overview of ESP32


| Feature               | Details                                                         |
| --------------------- | --------------------------------------------------------------- |
| **Manufacturer**      | Espressif Systems (China)                                       |
| **Processor**         | Dual-core Tensilica Xtensa LX6 (32-bit)                         |
| **Clock Speed**       | Up to 240 MHz                                                   |
| **Flash / SRAM**      | 4 MB Flash (external) / ~520 KB SRAM                            |
| **Connectivity**      | Wi-Fi (802.11 b/g/n), Bluetooth v4.2 + BLE                      |
| **Operating Voltage** | 3.3V                                                            |
| **I/O Pins**          | ~30 GPIOs (configurable as ADC, DAC, UART, SPI, I²C, PWM, etc.) |
| **ADC/DAC**           | 12-bit ADC (up to 18 channels), 2 × 8-bit DAC                   |
| **Timers**            | Hardware and software timers                                    |
| **PWM**               | 16 channels                                                     |



⚙️ 2. Architecture Highlights

Dual-core CPU (can use 1 for tasks and 1 for Wi-Fi/Bluetooth stack).

FreeRTOS-based — RTOS is integrated inside the SDK.

ROM Bootloader present — supports UART flashing.

Has on-chip RTC, temperature sensor, and touch sensors.

Integrated TCP/IP stack for networking.







